# Figma Design System Rules — my-portfolio

## Codebase Analysis Summary

This document captures design system conventions derived from analyzing the portfolio codebase. Use these rules when translating Figma designs to code.

---

## 1. Token Definitions

### Where Tokens Are Defined

- **Primary:** `src/index.css` — root-level CSS variables
- **Secondary:** `src/styles/global.css` — colors, background, text

### Token Format

```css
/* src/index.css :root */
--DarkSurface: #03070D;
--DarkElevation: #15191E;
--Light: #DFDAD8;
--Gray-3: #828282;
--Gray-4: #BDBDBD;
```

```css
/* src/styles/global.css :root */
--primary: #6b46c1;
--background: #121212;
--text: #dfdad8;
--text-muted: #bdbdbd;
```

### Token Usage Rules

- IMPORTANT: Prefer `var(--DarkSurface)`, `var(--Gray-3)`, `var(--Gray-4)` over hardcoded hex colors when matching the dark theme
- Background surfaces: `#03070D` (DarkSurface), `#15191E` (DarkElevation)
- Text: `#dfdad8`, `#d8d8d8`, `#ffffff` for primary/emphasis; `#828282`, `#BDBDBD` for muted
- Borders: `#3A3A3A`, `#272727`
- No formal token transformation system — use existing CSS variables

---

## 2. Component Library

### Location

- Reusable UI: `src/components/`
- Page views: `src/Views/` (Home, About, Projects/*)

### Component Architecture

- Functional components with TypeScript interfaces
- Use `React.FC<Props>` typing
- Props interfaces defined above or beside components
- Export default

### Existing Components (Reuse, Don't Recreate)

| Component | Path | Notes |
|-----------|------|-------|
| Button | `src/components/Button.tsx` | Variants: `text-only`, `icon-only`, `icon-and-text`; props: `label`, `icon`, `onClick`, `isActive`, `onlight` |
| Card | `src/components/Card.tsx` | `viewMode`: `large` \| `tiles` \| `list`; props: `title`, `imageUrl`, `viewMode` |
| Header | `src/components/Header.tsx` | Props: `title`, `imageSrc`, `imageAlt`, `details` (array of `{label, value}`) |
| Navbar | `src/components/Navbar.tsx` | Fixed nav with logo + links |
| Footer | `src/components/Footer.tsx` | Uses Button for links |
| Accordion | `src/components/Accordion.tsx` | Props: `items` (array of `{title, content}`); uses lucide-react ChevronDown |

### Component Patterns

- Place new components in `src/components/` with co-located `ComponentName.module.css`
- Use CSS Modules: `import styles from './ComponentName.module.css'`
- Apply classes: `className={styles.className}` or `className={\`${styles.base} ${styles[variant]}\`}`

---

## 3. Frameworks & Libraries

- **UI:** React 18
- **Routing:** react-router-dom
- **Build:** Vite 5, @vitejs/plugin-react
- **SVG:** vite-plugin-svgr (SVG as React components)
- **No Tailwind** — use CSS Modules only

---

## 4. Asset Management

### Storage

- Static assets in `public/` (served from root)
- Project-specific images in `public/assets/`

### Reference Rules

- Use root-relative paths: `/assets/Logo.svg`, `/proj2.png`, `/SunDay.png`
- Do NOT use `public/` prefix in `src` (e.g. use `/proj2.png`, not `public/proj2.png`)
- For images in Views: `./assets/` or `/assets/` depending on context (both resolve correctly when Vite serves from public)

### Asset Handling for Figma

- IMPORTANT: If the Figma MCP server returns a localhost source for an image or SVG, use that source directly
- IMPORTANT: DO NOT add new icon packages — use lucide-react, react-icons, or assets from Figma payload
- Store downloaded Figma assets in `public/assets/`

---

## 5. Icon System

### Sources

- **lucide-react:** Primary icon library — `import { ChevronDown, Volume2 } from "lucide-react"`
- **react-icons:** Available in package.json
- **SVG files:** Use vite-plugin-svgr; import as React component: `import Logo from '/assets/Logo.svg'`
- **Img for SVGs:** Also acceptable: `<img src="/assets/Logo.svg" alt="Logo" />`

### Usage Pattern

```tsx
import { ChevronDown } from "lucide-react"
<ChevronDown size={24} className={styles.icon} />
```

### Naming

- PascalCase for React icon components
- kebab-case for file names (e.g. `icon-pack.png`)

---

## 6. Styling Approach

### Methodology

- **CSS Modules** (`.module.css`) for all components and views
- **Global styles:** `src/index.css`, `src/App.css`, `src/styles/global.css`

### Typography

- **Primary:** `"IBM Plex Sans", sans-serif`
- **Monospace:** `"IBM Plex Mono", monospace`
- Fonts loaded via Google Fonts in `global.css`: IBM Plex Mono (400, 500), IBM Plex Sans (300, 400, 500)

### Responsive Breakpoints

- `@media (max-width: 1200px)` — tablet / smaller desktop
- `@media (max-width: 768px)` — mobile primary breakpoint
- `@media (max-width: 480px)` — small mobile

### Styling Rules

- Use CSS custom properties for colors where tokens exist
- Border radius: `8px`, `12px`, `100px` (for pills/buttons)
- Transitions: `0.2s ease-in-out`, `0.3s ease` for hover/interaction
- Flexbox and CSS Grid for layout (e.g. bento grid: `grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr`)

